text: Shinma Aungphyu (; ), also known as Phyaleit Nat (; ), is a prominent Burmese nat. She is commonly depicted wearing thanakha, donning a scarf and a htamein, and carrying a rolled up mat, hence her moniker Phyaleit Nat, which literally means "rolled mat." ==References== Category:Burmese nats Category:Burmese goddesses
title: Shinma Aungphyu
